## 1. Project Overview

This system performs **real-time person re-identification and multi-object tracking** in warehouse CCTV footage. It answers the question:

> *"When a worker walks out of frame and comes back, can we automatically recognise them as the same person and assign the same ID?"*

**Core capabilities:**
- Detects people + warehouse objects (forklifts, pallets, trucks, etc.) using a custom-trained **YOLOX-s** model
- Tracks every detected entity across frames using **ByteTrack** (motion + IoU)
- Extracts 512-dimensional appearance embeddings for each person using **OSNet** (deep Re-ID neural network)
- Matches embeddings against a persistent **gallery** — so `person_1` stays `person_1` even after re-entering the scene
- Enforces **one-to-one uniqueness per frame** — two different people in the same frame can never share an ID
- Runs on **NVIDIA GPU (CUDA)** for real-time speed

