## 2. System Architecture

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                    Input Video                       │
│            (.mp4 / RTSP / uploaded file)             │
└───────────────────────┬─────────────────────────────┘
                        │ frame (BGR numpy array)
                        ▼
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│              core/detector.py  (YOLOX-s)            │
│  • Preprocesses frame to 640×640                    │
│  • Runs inference → raw detections                  │
│  • NMS + confidence filtering                       │
│  • Splits output into:                              │
│       persons []   ←  class_id == 0                 │
│       objects []   ←  all other classes             │
└──────────────┬────────────────────┬─────────────────┘
               │ person_dets        │ object_dets
               ▼                    ▼
┌──────────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────────────┐
│  PersonTracker       │  │  ObjectTracker            │
│  ByteTrack           │  │  ByteTrack                │
│  (Motion + IoU)      │  │  (Motion + IoU only)      │
│  → track_id, bbox,   │  │  → track_id, bbox, conf,  │
│    conf, crop        │  │    class_id               │
└──────────┬───────────┘  └──────────────────────────┘
           │ person tracks (with image crops)
           ▼
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│              core/reid.py  (OSNet-x1_0)             │
│  • Resizes crop to 256×128                          │
│  • ImageNet normalization                           │
│  • Forward pass → 512-d feature vector             │
│  • L2 normalization                                 │
└───────────────────────┬─────────────────────────────┘
                        │ 512-d embedding per person
                        ▼
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│              core/memory.py  (ReID Gallery)         │
│                                                     │
│  begin_frame(active_track_ids)                      │
│    → resets frame-uniqueness set                    │
│    → purges dead track→person mappings              │
│                                                     │
│  match(embedding, track_id)                         │
│    1. Fast path: track already matched? → return    │
│    2. Expire TTL entries                            │
│    3. Cosine similarity vs all gallery entries      │
│       (skip IDs already used this frame)            │
│    4. score >= threshold → existing person          │
│       score <  threshold → NEW person_N             │
│    5. EMA-update gallery embedding                  │
│    6. Cache track_id → person_id                    │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
                        │ person_id (stable)
                        ▼
              Final Result per Frame:
              persons: [{track_id, person_id, label, bbox, conf}]
              objects: [{track_id, class_id, bbox, conf}]
```

