## 8. Known Limitations

| Limitation | Details |
|---|---|
| **~7-8 FPS on RTX 3050** | YOLOX and OSNet both run sequentially on CPU→GPU. Could reach 15–25 FPS with batch inference or model quantization (TensorRT). |
| **Re-ID under heavy occlusion** | If a person is hidden for longer than `track_buffer` frames AND their gallery TTL expires, they will get a new ID. Increase `track_buffer` and `ttl_seconds` to mitigate. |
| **Similar-looking people** | Workers in identical uniforms + helmets may match each other's gallery entries. Raise `cosine_threshold` to 0.80+ to be stricter (at cost of more new IDs on re-entry). |
| **YOLOX custom classes** | The detector is trained on warehouse-specific classes only. It will not detect people in significantly different environments without retraining. |
| **No person count deduplication** | The "Persons: 7" overlay counts active ByteTrack tracks, not unique gallery entries. |
